array.string: Squat Hold
1. Move feet shoulder length apart 2. While keeping knees inline with feet and back straight, bend knees 3. Hold in bent position
Squat Pulse
1. Move feet shoulder length apart 2. While keeping knees inline with feet and back straight, bend knees 3. Move slightly up and down while keeping deep bend in knees
One Leg Step-Ups

1. Find raised surface 2. Place one foot on raised surface 3. Transfer weight to foot on raised surface 4. Once standing on raised surface, bring knee of non-weight bearing foot up so that femur is parallel to ground 5. Step non-weight bearing foot back onto ground
One Leg Back Lunges
1. Shift weight onto one foot 2. Step backwards with non-weight bearing so that weight bearing knee is at 90 degree angle 3. Press back to standing
Air Squats
1. Move feet shoulder length apart 2. While keeping knees inline with feet and back straight, bend knees 3. Press back to straight legs
Squat Jumps
1. Move feet shoulder length apart 2. While keeping knees inline with feet and back straight, bend knees 3. Press into feet to jump
Pistol Squats

1. If needed, find raised surface 2. Shift weight onto one leg 3. Bend weight bearing leg as far as possible (or until touch raised surface), non-weight bearing foot hovers slightly above ground 4. Press back to straight leg
One Leg Forward Lunges
1. Shift weight onto one foot 2. Step forwards with non-weight bearing so that forward knee is at 90 degree angle 3. Press back to standing
One Leg Side Lunges
1. Shift weight onto one foot 2. Step sideways with non-weight bearing so that side stepping knee is at 90 degree angle 3. Press back to standing
Burpees
1. Begin in standing position 2. Jump upwards 3. Put hands onto ground 4. Kick legs backwards into plank position 5. Do a pushup 6. Jump legs forward to hands 7. Stand up
Calf Lifts

1. Find a raised surface 2. Stand on raised surface so that heals are hanging off edge 3. Shift weight to one foot, hover non-weight bearing foot just over ground 4. Press into toes of weight bearing foot to lift heal 5. Lower heal back down
Box Jumps
1. Find a raised surface 2. With knees shoulder length apart, jump onto raised surface 3. Jump back down, landing with feet shoulder length apart
Box Toe Touches
1. Find raised surface 2. Put toes of one foot on raised surface 3. Quickly switch to toes of other foot touching raised surface
